{"id":10872,"date":"2013-01-02T13:23:45","date_gmt":"2013-01-02T18:23:45","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=10872"},"modified":"2023-03-09T15:00:33","modified_gmt":"2023-03-09T11:00:33","slug":"ahl-al-kitab-believers","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/02\/ahl-al-kitab-believers\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Ahl Kitab: Among People of the Book are righteous believers"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, delayed the evening prayer, then he later came out to the mosque to find people waiting for the prayer. The Prophet said, \u201c<b>Are there none among the people of these religions remembering Allah at this hour besides you<\/b>?\u201d Then, Allah revealed these verses, \u201c<strong>Not all of them are the same. Among the People of the Book is an upright nation, reciting the verses of Allah by night and prostrating in prayer. They have faith in Allah and the Last Day, they enjoin good and forbid evil, and they race to all that is good. These are among the righteous and whatever they do will never be denied, for Allah knows well those who fear Him.<\/strong>&#8221;\u00a0(3:113-115)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 3760<\/p>\n<p>Grade:\u00a0<b><i>Sahih li ghayrihi <\/i><\/b>(authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Arna&#8217;ut<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0651\u0631\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0629\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u0650\u0634\u064e\u